=head1 NAME

aperl516 - execute perlscript on ActivePerl 5.8 without %PATH% settings (poor App::perlbrew)

=head1 SYNOPSIS

B<aperl516> [perlscript.pl]

=head1 DESCRIPTION

This software is useful when ActivePerl 5.8 and other version of perl are on the one
computer. Do not set perl5.16's bin directory to %PATH%.

It is necessary to install perl5.16 in "\Perl516\bin" directory of the drive of
either. This software is executed by perl5.16, and find the perl5.16 and execute it.

 Find perl5.16 order by,
     Z:\Perl516\bin\perl.exe
     Y:\Perl516\bin\perl.exe
     X:\Perl516\bin\perl.exe
                 :
                 :
     C:\Perl516\bin\perl.exe

When found it at last, set its path to environment variable APERL516BIN.

=head1 EXAMPLES

    C:\> aperl516 foo.pl
    [..execute foo.pl by perl5.16..]

